OL,3,CHomelessness in England rises by more
OL,4,Cthan 12% in past year
OL,6,FHomelessness in England has increased
OL,7,Fby more than 12% in the past year,
OL,8,Fwith a stark rise in the number of
OL,9,Fhouseholds living in temporary
OL,10,Faccommodation, according to government
OL,11,Fstatistics.
OL,13,FIn the year leading up to March 2024,
OL,14,F178,560 households were assessed as
OL,15,Fhomeless.
OL,17,FIt marks a 12.3% increase on the
OL,18,Fprevious financial year, according to
OL,19,Fnew government figures.
