OL,3,CHomelessness in England rises by more
OL,4,Cthan 12% in past year
OL,6,FShelter said the data, published on
OL,7,FThursday by the government, shows that
OL,8,Fthe "housing emergency has trapped
OL,9,Fmany families in temporary
OL,10,Faccommodation for over five years".
OL,12,FThe number of households with children
OL,13,Fin temporary accommodation, which is a
OL,14,Fform of homelessness, increased by
OL,15,F14.7% to 74,530.
OL,17,FNearly a quarter (23%) of families in
OL,18,Ftemporary accommodation have been
OL,19,Fliving there for more than five years
OL,20,F` this is a 24% increase in one year.
