OL,6,FAt age 18, when she realised she was
OL,7,Fgoing to be homeless, she contacted
OL,8,Fher local authority for support and
OL,9,Fwas moved into supported accommodation.
OL,11,FShe said there were issues, such as
OL,12,Fviolence, at the accommodation.
OL,13,FWindows wouldn't close, and the
OL,14,Fradiators were on 365 days a year.
OL,16,FShe said she was told to stay there
OL,17,Fand the council would find her
OL,18,Fsomething else, but nothing came.
OL,20,F"I don't feel there's enough support,"
OL,21,Fshe told ITV News.
